<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 01 at 11:00PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Gray and
Donley Counties through 1130 PM CDT...
At 1100 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles west of Lake Mcclellan, or 18 miles north of Clarendon, moving
east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Clarendon, Mclean, Howardwick, Alanreed, Lake Mcclellan and Greenbelt
Lake.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
